text: Victoria Monét McCants (born May 1, 1993) is an American singer-songwriter. Monét has written songs for many singer such as Nas, Ariana Grande, Fifth Harmony, T.I., GOOD Music, Lupe Fiasco, Chrisette Michele, Coco Jones, Chris Brown, and Diddy Dirty Money. In 2019, Monét received two Grammy Award nominations for Album of the Year for her work on Grande's Thank U, Next and Record of the Year for "7 Rings". ==References== Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:American singer-songwriters Category:American pop singers Category:American R&B; singers Category:Singers from Georgia (U.S. state) Category:Writers from Georgia (U.S. state) Category:Singers from Sacramento, California Category:Writers from Sacramento, California
